The paper deals with updates to logic programs, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses principles that constrain the interaction between strong and default negation, which is a topic in logic (cs.LO). The paper proposes an extension to an existing semantics, which is a software engineering task (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with rule updates, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL).
